==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gerah
<hw>Ge"rah</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>g<?/rah</ets>, lit., a bean.]</ety> <fld>(Jewish Antiq.)</fld>
<def>A small coin and weight; 1-20th of a shekel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The silver gerah is supposed to have been worth about
three cents; the gold about fifty-four cents; the weight equivalent to
about thirteen grains.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Geraniaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
